name: svia
normalized: …this place is…
valkyrie svia awoke to a minor concussion.
her mind was foggy, like it was caught in a haze…
svia felt as if she had been dreaming.
the girl halfway between sleep and consciousness slowly surveyed the area around her.
a pretentious voice reached her ears.

name: loki
normalized: the citrus of this wine that catches in your throat is hard to replace… drinking this fills my heart.
it was loki.
he drank his glass of wine, wiped his mouth, and stated his impressions.

name: svia
normalized: loki…

name: loki
normalized: so you finally woke up?
noble pricynthia svia?

name: svia
normalized: (come to think of it, that used to be my name, too…)
princess pricynthia svia.
it was the proof that she was a high-class noble before she became a valkyrie.
to her, it was a foolish name which boasted of her family line's exaltedness.
svia moved only her eyes and confirmed the situation she'd been placed in.

name: svia
normalized: (it looks like… the underworld's prison.
in the prison, just like svia, sigurd also had her ankles bound in chains.
she confirmed that they had been captured, then immediately realized they had been been caught in a trap that made them dream via loki's magic.

name: loki
normalized: all life in this world dreams.
hel, the jotnar, the divine, humans… oh, even the animals, insects, and vegetation.

name: sigurd
normalized: when did things cease to be real!?
sigurd, who had woken up as svia had, raised her voice to loki.

name: loki
normalized: calm down.
it's not good to be rash.
loki raised his hand and commanded the exasperated sigurd.

name: svia
normalized: i see, loki.
i was a step above, but you were another step above that, huh?

name: loki
normalized: no, miss pricynthia.
you are indeed on the ball.
at any rate, i was deceived, as well.

name: svia
normalized: quit using that name.
i'm valkyrie svia.
svia for certain did not show it on her face, but her voice showed her unhappiness.

name: loki
normalized: did i make you angry?
come now, svia.
it was indeed a good strategy.
more an art than a strategy.
no opera, no matter how fine, has ever moved me so much.

name: sigurd
normalized: answer me, loki!
unlike svia, sigurd barked with her emotions bared.

name: loki
normalized: hmph, very well.
i'll have flungruni give your answer.
loki finished speaking, and flungruni sluggishly made his way into the prison.

name: flungruni
normalized: damn.
you fricking valkyries really mangled me.

name: flungruni
normalized: i've been patched up, but the going is still rough thanks to you.

name: flungruni
normalized: especially you, sigurd.
taking off my head… i'll have you make up for that later in spades.
flungruni said as he crackled his head.
it was still not completely attached, and she winced at the unsettling feeling inside her.
svia looked at flungruni and opened her mouth derisively, realizing now just when loki's magic had kicked in.

name: svia
normalized: so the illusion kicked in once we left flungruni's room.

name: loki
normalized: correct.
what do you think of being led to this blood-smeared cellar in the underworldly plane as your reward?

name: svia
normalized: no thanks.
svia keenly realized she had been negligent in the last leg of her plan.
she had made sigurd think her a foe, was brought in by the unprudent flungruni, and crept to his side.
and then, she stabbed him to death as planned, and even retrieved gungnir according to calculations.
however, svia had overlooked the fact that loki had seen it all.
but loki had not overlooked it.
had not overlooked this ideal chance, where two valkyries had landed right in his pocket.
the moment they left the room, he had bewitched svia and sigurd.
none the wiser, they rescued odin and revived the world tree, and experienced true euphoria in their dreams.
svia thought herself a fool and sighed internally.

name: svia
normalized: so you managed to capture the valkyries alive, huh?

name: loki
normalized: indeed.
however, at great cost.
i had to cobble flungruni back together.
you made me waste a whole night on that.

name: flungruni
normalized: all right.
now, then, it's high time we extracted those keys.
uhah, loki.
i'll take sigurd.
i won't be satisfied until i get her nice and sticky.

name: flungruni
normalized: that's okay, yes?
there was passion on his face.

name: loki
normalized: it's no problem.
sigurd, i'll be praying for your good luck.
loki revealed a ruthless smile and gave his permission.

name: sigurd
normalized: damn it… i won't let things go the way you want!

name: flungruni
normalized: okay, i'll transfer her to a different prison.
first, you're getting a good spanking!
flungruni's subordinate jotnars came and took her away.

name: sigurd
normalized: release me!
though sigurd desperately resisted, she was outmatched three to one.

name: sigurd
normalized: svia!
sigurd stared at her as she was nearly out of sight.

name: sigurd
normalized: don't give in.
i won't, either.
svia showed no expression and slowly nodded.
and then, sigurd was taken away.
svia and loki were alone in the gloomy jail cell.

name: loki
normalized: now then.
as a result, i'm now in the unsavory position of watching you, but… i really have no interest.
loki said and smiled.

name: svia
normalized: then why don't you just stop?
there's no need to do something you don't find interesting.
there are many in this underworldly plane that would jump at the chance to kill a valkyrie, aren't there?
svia replied indifferently, still expressionless.

name: loki
normalized: so you're prepared, then?
svia looked at loki with just an expressionless face, without confirming or denying, as he sneered once again.

name: loki
normalized: valkyrie svia.
no, i'll call you this one more time… princess pricynthia.

name: loki
normalized: do you remember?

name: loki
normalized: that day, my marriage ceremony.
holding the hem of my now ex-wife's dress against your will.

name: loki
normalized: as she sparkled in a pure white dress, looking oh so charming, you grumbled as my ex-wife stole the spotlight.

name: svia
normalized: i remember it.
one utterly worthless memory.
svia spat, looking truly uninterested.

name: loki
normalized: i remember it well, too.
you looked bored indeed.

name: loki
normalized: i had an interest in you because of it.
loki said that as he sized up svia closely.

name: loki
normalized: do you remember afterward, at the royal court's dinner party, where i took your hand and kissed you?

name: svia
normalized: that was a bother.

name: loki
normalized: likely so.
you were engrossed in a book about the war strategies of the orient.

name: loki
normalized: that book certainly was interesting.
quite rational for a novel.
i coveted it in my youth.

name: loki
normalized: but, it was a bit much for the daughter of the noble pricynthia household to be reading.

name: svia
normalized: that's why i threw that all away.
being an aristocrat was the more tedious social position.
svia said that quite readily, without letting emotion smear her voice.
svia did not show emotion, and thus had always been considered a bit of a character.
but when she noticed loki's true intent, she dared pierce that tone.
loki's tone wasn't one which was pointed at an enemy, but one which would try to so perfectly make a woman his.

name: svia
normalized: will you make advances on women, no matter who, at any time?

name: loki
normalized: of course.
loki replied immediately and jerked back the hands behind svia's back.
however, svia did not lose her stature.

name: loki
normalized: and… i'll make any woman serve me.
loki pasted on a cruel smirk.
this was his true nature.

name: svia
normalized: i'm not a woman.
i'm a valkyrie.
svia was undaunted and denied the fact she was a woman.

name: loki
normalized: no, no.
you're still the same as you were back then in my mind.
he tugged svia toward him and smiled again.
svia silently looked at loki's smiling face and showed no expression whatsoever.
